\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Disk-disk contact force $F_{\rm  dd}(\delta )$ vs.\ overlap $\delta /R_0$ on log-log axes (top row) and fractional residuals of the power-law fit $A\delta ^n$ (bottom row), for three Poisson ratios (columns) and all five resolutions $N \in \{32,48,72,120,240\}$. Solid lines are measured data; dashed lines of matching colour are the fitted $A\delta ^n$. Reference slopes $n=1$ (linear DEM, dotted) and $n=1.5$ (3D Hertz, dash-dot) are shown in the rightmost panel. Residuals are computed over $\delta > 0.2\,\delta _{\rm  max}$ to exclude the discrete contact-onset transient. Fit quality is $\lesssim 5\%$ for $N \geq 72$ across the full overlap range; the larger deviations at $N = 32$ reflect the coarse node-entry steps visible as kinks in the solid curve.}}{10}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fd_fits}{{8}{10}{Disk-disk contact force $F_{\rm dd}(\delta )$ vs.\ overlap $\delta /R_0$ on log-log axes (top row) and fractional residuals of the power-law fit $A\delta ^n$ (bottom row), for three Poisson ratios (columns) and all five resolutions $N \in \{32,48,72,120,240\}$. Solid lines are measured data; dashed lines of matching colour are the fitted $A\delta ^n$. Reference slopes $n=1$ (linear DEM, dotted) and $n=1.5$ (3D Hertz, dash-dot) are shown in the rightmost panel. Residuals are computed over $\delta > 0.2\,\delta _{\rm max}$ to exclude the discrete contact-onset transient. Fit quality is $\lesssim 5\%$ for $N \geq 72$ across the full overlap range; the larger deviations at $N = 32$ reflect the coarse node-entry steps visible as kinks in the solid curve}{figure.8}{}}
